Lake Mead Hoover Dam and Powerplant.Vertical Datum Description: Elevations are referenced to the United States Geological Survey datum, adjustment of 1912, locally known as “Power House Datum.” One can add 0.55 feet to convert to the National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929, leveling of 1935 (NGVD27).

Brantley Reservoir and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: Brantley reservoir was built to NGVD 29 datum, however the elevations used herein are NAVD 88 because storages posted to the internet use that datum. Conversion factor NAVD 88 to NGVD 29 is 1.6 ft.

Avalon Reservoir and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: Built over 100 years ago to local datum, approximately 14 feet difference from NGVD 29.

Lake Sumner and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: The vertical "as built" drawings are Project Datum, but for capacity I'm using the NAVD 88 because that is what is shown on the internet. To get Project Datum subtract 1.88 ft from the elevations above.

Clear Lake Reservoir.Vertical Datum Description: Historical BOR datum has been referenced

El Vado Lake and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: The vertical datum is called RVPD or Reclamation Vertical Project Datum.

Fresno Reservoir and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: Reclamation project vertical  datum established during construction and confirmed to be 4.7 feet higher than National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929 (NGVD29)

Lake Sherburne and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: RPVD was was found to be 9.45 feet lower than the National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929 (NGVD29) and 13.75 feet lower than the North American Vertical Datum of 1988 (NAVD88).

Nelson Reservoir and Nelson Dikes.Vertical Datum Description: RPVD is 1.70 feet lower than National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929.

Lake Havasu Parker Dam and Powerplant.Vertical Datum Description: Elevations are referenced to the United States Geological Survey datum, adjustment of 1912, locally known as “Power House Datum.” One can add 0.55 feet to convert to the National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929, leveling of 1935 (NGVD27).

Lake Mohave Davis Dam and Powerplant.Vertical Datum Description: Elevations are referenced to the United States Geological Survey datum, adjustment of 1912, locally known as “Power House Datum.” One can add 0.55 feet to convert to the National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929, leveling of 1935 (NGVD27).

Lake Elwell and Tiber Dam.Vertical Datum Description: RPVD was determined to be 2.9 feet lower than the North American Vertical Datum of 1988 (NAVD88).

Canyon Ferry Lake Dam Powerplant and Hel.Vertical Datum Description: Reclamation Project Vertical Datum (RVPD), which is 0.08 feet lower than National Geodetic Vertical Datum (NGVD) of 1929 and 3.15 feet lower than North American Vertical Datum (NAVD) of 1988.

Bonny Reservoir and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: RPVD is 1.1 feet lower than the NAVD88 and 0.5 feet higher than the National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929 (NGVD29).

Glendo Reservoir Dam and Powerplant.Vertical Datum Description: The 2003 survey found Reclamation's datum to be around 2.55 feet less than the North American Vertical Datum of 1988 (NAVD88).

Yellowtail Afterbay and Yellowtail After.Vertical Datum Description: RPVD is 2.8 feet lower than North American Vertical Datum of 1988 NAVD88.

Waconda Lake and Glen Elder Dam.Vertical Datum Description: RPVD is 1.2 feet greater then the NGVD29

Caballo Reservoir and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: Project datum is 43.3 lower than NGVD 29

Elephant Butte Reservoir Dam and Powerpl.Vertical Datum Description: Project datum is -43.3 ft lower than NGVD 29

Heron Reservoir and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: From the 2010 ACAP: All data for these tables are tied to the project vertical datum that is NGVD29 and 4.3 feet less than NAVD88

Gibson Reservoir and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: Reclamation Project Vertical Datum established during construction and confirmed by this study to be 7.5 feet lower than the North American Vertical Datum of 1988 (NAVD88)

Pishkun Reservoir and Dikes.Vertical Datum Description: RPVD is 6.4 feet lower than the North American Vertical Datum of 1988 (NAVD88).

Sun River Diversion Dam.Vertical Datum Description: Reclamation Project Vertical Datum, measured 7.5 lower than NAVD88

Willow Creek Reservoir and Dam (MT).Vertical Datum Description: RPVD is 3.4 feet lower than the National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929 (NGVD29) and 6.7 feet lower than North American Vertical Datum of 1988 NAVD88.

Foss Reservoir and Dam.Vertical Datum Description: The project vertical datum appears to be around 0.3 higher than NGVD29 and 0.5 feet lower than NAVD88.
